The one who dares to disturb
Lord Ankh'remun in his eternal sleep
shall forever regret it
for he shall suffer a death
that is a thousand times worse!

"I am Ankh'remun, lord of the city which bears the same name.
  Foolish is he who cometh, seeking my treasures and riches
for he shall only find woe and death.
  May the sands of time decieve him, and cast him into
the deepest pits of hell!"
Here lies Nes'ek, the loyal servant of Ankh'remun. May he find peace in the afterlife.
Whether for good or ill, some creature lies here, long undisturbed.
